=== Other Notable Otaue Festivals === * {{ill|Tsutsukowake Shrine|ja|都々古別神社|12=draft|12=draft}}’s Otaue Festival in {{ill|Tanakura|ja|棚倉町|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Fukushima Prefecture|ja|福島県|12=draft|12=draft}} (Important Intangible Folk Cultural Property). * The Otaue Festival of {{ill|Keitoku Inari Shrine|ja|慶徳稲荷神社|12=draft|12=draft}} in {{ill|Kitakata|ja|喜多方市|12=draft|12=draft}}, Fukushima Prefecture (Important Intangible Folk Cultural Property). * {{ill|Isasumi Shrine|ja|伊佐須美神社|12=draft|12=draft}} in {{ill|Aizu Misato|ja|会津美里町|1=Aizumisato|12=draft|12=draft}}, Fukushima Prefecture (Important Intangible Folk Cultural Property). * {{ill|Chichibu Shrine|ja|秩父神社|12=draft|12=draft}}’s {{ill|Chichibu Shrine Otaue Matsuri|ja|秩父神社御田植祭|12=draft|12=draft}} in {{ill|Chichibu|ja|秩父市|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Saitama Prefecture|ja|埼玉県|12=draft|12=draft}} (designated as a Saitama Prefectural Cultural Property). * {{ill|Shimo-mura Kamo Shrine|ja|下村加茂神社|12=draft|12=draft}} in {{ill|Imizu|ja|射水市|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Toyama Prefecture|ja|富山県|12=draft|12=draft}} (designated as a Toyama Prefectural Cultural Property and selected for the Toyama Cultural Heritage 100). * {{ill|Hirohata Shrine|ja|広峯神社|12=draft|12=draft}} in {{ill|Himeji|ja|姫路市|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Hyōgo Prefecture|ja|兵庫県|12=draft|12=draft}} (designated as a Himeji City Intangible Cultural Property). * {{ill|Kibitsu-hiko Shrine|ja|吉備津彦神社|12=draft|12=draft}} in {{ill|Okayama|ja|岡山市|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Okayama Prefecture|ja|岡山県|12=draft|12=draft}}. * {{ill|Fuse Shrine|ja|布勢神社|12=draft|12=draft}} in {{ill|Ōkita|ja|東区|12=draft|12=draft}}, Okayama Prefecture (designated as an Important Intangible Cultural Property).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://afw-at.com/page_e.php?id=432|title=Fuse Shrine Otaue Festival|publisher=At Town Web Magazine|accessdate=2019-03-28}}</ref> * {{ill|Wakamiya Hachiman Shrine (Kitsuki)|ja|若宮八幡社|12=draft|12=draft}} in {{ill|Kitsuki|ja|杵築市|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Ōita Prefecture|ja|大分県|12=draft|12=draft}} (designated as an Ōita Prefectural Cultural Property).
