=== Other Notable Otaue Festivals === * {{ill|Tsutsukowake Shrine|ja|都々古別神社}}’s Otaue Festival in {{ill|Tanakura|ja|棚倉町}}, {{ill|Fukushima Prefecture|ja|福島県}} (Important Intangible Folk Cultural Property). * The Otaue Festival of {{ill|Keitoku Inari Shrine|ja|慶徳稲荷神社}} in {{ill|Kitakata|ja|喜多方市}}, Fukushima Prefecture (Important Intangible Folk Cultural Property). * {{ill|Isasumi Shrine|ja|伊佐須美神社}} in {{ill|Aizu Misato|ja|Aizumisato|1=Aizumisato}}, Fukushima Prefecture (Important Intangible Folk Cultural Property). * {{ill|Chichibu Shrine|ja|秩父神社}}’s {{ill|Chichibu Shrine Otaue Matsuri|ja|秩父神社御田植祭}} in {{ill|Chichibu|ja|秩父市}}, {{ill|Saitama Prefecture|ja|埼玉県}} (designated as a Saitama Prefectural Cultural Property). * {{ill|Shimo-mura Kamo Shrine|ja|下村加茂神社}} in {{ill|Imizu|ja|射水市}}, {{ill|Toyama Prefecture|ja|富山県}} (designated as a Toyama Prefectural Cultural Property and selected for the Toyama Cultural Heritage 100). * {{ill|Hirohata Shrine|ja|広峯神社}} in {{ill|Himeji|ja|姫路市}}, {{ill|Hyōgo Prefecture|ja|兵庫県}} (designated as a Himeji City Intangible Cultural Property). * {{ill|Kibitsu-hiko Shrine|ja|吉備津彦神社}} in {{ill|Okayama|ja|岡山市}}, {{ill|Okayama Prefecture|ja|岡山県}}. * {{ill|Fuse Shrine|ja|布勢神社}} in {{ill|Ōkita|ja|東区}}, Okayama Prefecture (designated as an Important Intangible Cultural Property).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://afw-at.com/page_e.php?id=432|title=Fuse Shrine Otaue Festival|publisher=At Town Web Magazine|accessdate=2019-03-28}}</ref> * {{ill|Wakamiya Hachiman Shrine (Kitsuki)|ja|若宮八幡社}} in {{ill|Kitsuki|ja|杵築市}}, {{ill|Ōita Prefecture|ja|大分県}} (designated as an Ōita Prefectural Cultural Property).
== References == {{Reflist}} == See Also == * {{ill|Theatre of Japan|lt=Theatre of Japan|lt=Traditional performing arts of Japan|ja|伝統芸能|en}} * {{ill|Dengaku|ja|田楽}} * {{ill|Taue Odori|ja|田植踊}} * {{ill|Ota-mai|ja|御田舞}} * {{ill|List of festivals in Japan|ja|日本の祭一覧}}
== Further Reading == * 『年中行事大辞典』 (Comprehensive Encyclopedia of Annual Events) (Yoshikawa Kōbunkan, 2009). ISBN 978-4-642-01443-4. * 『とやまの文化財百選シリーズ(3) とやまの祭り』 (Toyama’s 100 Cultural Treasures, Series 3: Festivals) (Toyama Prefectural Board of Education, 2007).
